# Next.js server package

- **Next.js 15** App Router app under `server/src/app/`.
- Acts as the **data gateway** for the client (see `.cursor/rules/server-data-gateway.mdc`).
- Today: `GET /api/health`, `GET /api/openapi.json` (system) + `POST /api/profiles`, `GET /api/budget`, `PUT /api/budget` (data, JWT-protected).
- Server uses Supabase **anon** key + the user's JWT (RLS still applies). Do not introduce `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` without an explicit admin use case.

## Conventions
- API routes: `server/src/app/api/<name>/route.ts`.
- Every JSON route exports `OPTIONS` → `corsPreflight(request)` and wraps responses with `withCors(request, ...)` (`server/src/lib/cors.ts`).
- Auth: get the user with `supabaseForRequest(request)` (`server/src/lib/supabase.ts`); short-circuit on `!ok`.
- Validate POST/PUT bodies; return 400 with `{ error, details }` on failure.
- DTOs come from `@wedding-hall/shared` — never invent a second copy.
- Update `server/src/lib/openapi.ts` when adding/changing routes.
